about the different ways

00:32:09.120 --> 00:32:13.500
in which you can actually do
interesting things with images.

00:32:13.500 --> 00:32:16.790
So we talked about some best
practices like how to show text

00:32:16.790 --> 00:32:21.190
overlays when showing
banner images or thumbnails.

00:32:21.190 --> 00:32:23.536
We talked about placeholders
in this example.

00:32:23.536 --> 00:32:24.910
We talked about
how Pintrest does

00:32:24.910 --> 00:32:29.940
a great job of actually keying
the placeholder a color,

00:32:29.940 --> 00:32:31.450
based on the image.

00:32:31.450 --> 00:32:34.880
So they actually-- it seems like
they store another bit almost

00:32:34.880 --> 00:32:39.290
in the database of the
key color in the image,

00:32:39.290 --> 00:32:42.100
and they show that color
before the image itself loads.

00:32:42.100 --> 00:32:44.900
So gives you a little
touch of context

00:32:44.900 --> 00:32:47.430
as to what's going to
show up in that space.

00:32:47.430 --> 00:32:50.550
We also talked about the
center cropping technique,

00:32:50.550 --> 00:32:55.260
which is a great way to
basically allow your U/Is

00:32:55.260 --> 00:32:58.210
to scale to different
aspect ratios.

00:32:58.210 --> 00:33:01.310
And in the center cropping
technique you basically--

00:33:01.310 --> 00:33:03.420
it's actually very
simple to use.

00:33:03.420 --> 00:33:05.820
You actually just set the
scale type to center crop

00:33:05.820 --> 00:33:07.740
on an image view.

00:33:07.740 --> 00:33:09.640
But in this technique,
you basically

00:33:09.640 --> 00:33:11.200
chop off either
the left and right

00:33:11.200 --> 00:33:14.630
or the top and
bottom of an image

00:33:14.630 --> 00:33:18.810
if the aspect ratio of the
image and its target destination

00:33:18.810 --> 00:33:20.550
don't match.

00:33:20.550 --> 00:33:22.610
And we also talked
about focus, things

00:33:22.610 --> 00:33:25.420
like using blurring
and dimming techniques

00:33:25.420 --> 00:33:28.990
to help the user really focus
on the most important things,

00:33:28.990 --> 00:33:33.270
whether it be the text in
front, or gray scaling an image

00:33:33.270 --> 00:33:35.489
if it's not important,
and things like that.

00:33:35.489 --> 00:33:37.030
So overall we just
touched on a bunch

00:33:37.030 --> 00:33:39.850
of different best practices
and a couple of ideas

00:33:39.850 --> 00:33:42.930
on how to present images.

