00:34:04.680 --> 00:34:07.530
of markers, basically
how you can introduce

00:34:07.530 --> 00:34:11.440
branding into something that
is from a shape standpoint.

00:34:11.440 --> 00:34:13.440
The shape of a marker
is generally pretty

00:34:13.440 --> 00:34:15.830
standard, but how
you can actually

00:34:15.830 --> 00:34:18.760
introduce some of your branding
into that as well as how

00:34:18.760 --> 00:34:19.790
to deal with density.

00:34:19.790 --> 00:34:21.679
If you have tons
and tons of markers,

00:34:21.679 --> 00:34:24.429
how can you actually
still allow the users

00:34:24.429 --> 00:34:26.850
to see the map underneath
all the markers?

00:34:26.850 --> 00:34:29.389
So we talked about
that for quite a bit.

00:34:29.389 --> 00:34:31.980
We talked about full screen,
